author: BILL PLUNKETT
title: Final: Dodgers routed by Mets in Game 3, pushed to brink of elimination
text: Final: Dodgers routed by Mets in Game 3, pushed to brink of elimination Oct. 12, 2015 Updated 9:27 p.m. 1 of 5 The Mets' Curtis Granderson hits a three-run double during the second inning of Monday's game against the Dodgers. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 Dodgers starting pitcher Brett Anderson reacts as the Mets Travis d'Arnaud, right, runs the bases after hitting a two-run home run during the third inning. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 The Mets' Yoenis Cespedes (52) greets teammate Travis d'Arnaud after scoring on d'Arnaud's two-run home run off Dodgers pitcher Brett Anderson during the third inning. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 The Dodgers' Yasmani Grandal hits a second-inning three-run single during Monday's Game 3 of the National League Division Series against the Mets. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 The Dodgers' Justin Turner, left, greets Carl Crawford as they celebrate with Andre Ethier after the trio scored on Yasmani Grandal's second inning three-run single against the Mets. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
